    "en": {
      "title": "A gazette is coming for health, petroleum and electricity",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe has issued a gazette notification to be effective from today (03), once again specifying the supply of intermittent power and all related services, petroleum production and fuel supply or distribution and health services as essential services for maintaining the normal life of the people. have",
        "Pursuant to the request made with the recommendations of the relevant Ministers of the Ministry of Health and the Ministry of Power to make the health service, petroleum and electricity essential services, under Section 2 of the Essential Public Services Act No. 61 of 1979, this Gazette Notice has been published in accordance with the powers assigned to the President. have.",
        "Earlier also, a notification dated 08-03-2022 was issued in accordance with the powers assigned to the President specifying these services as essential services.",
        "According to the provisions of Section 3(2) of the said Act, the Prime Minister's Secretary was instructed to take necessary steps to table a resolution in Parliament regarding the said Gazette Notification, and after the adoption of the resolution, the order remained valid for a period of one month. Accordingly, the validity period of the notification ended after 2022-09-02.",
        "Since a request was again submitted to the President with the recommendations of the ministers in charge of the subject, steps have been taken to declare the aforementioned services as essential services from September 3, 2022 through a gazette announcement."
      ],
